--[[
How can you check whether a value is
a boolean without using the function
`type()`?
--]]

Anything that isn't `nil` or `false` in
Lua is by default a "truthy" value.
Therefore you can use any logical statement:

```
print(not 0)    --> false
if 1 then print() end    --> "\n"
if not false then print() end    --> "\n"
```
